article.headline: Comets' 10-0 late run bury Silver Stars
article.linkText: Hey, 19! Snow, Thompson match scores in Comets' victory
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Michelle Snow and Tina Thompson came up big when
it mattered most.

Snow scored a career-high 19 points and added eight rebounds,
and Thompson added 19 points as Houston beat San Antonio 64-49 on
Saturday.

Gwen Jackson scored 15 points and Marie Ferdinand added 10 for
the Silver Stars (5-9).

Houston (7-7) led by as many as 19 points in the first half. But
the Silver Stars used an 11-5 run in the final 3:31 of the half to
close to 34-21 at the break. Snow led all scorers with 10 points at
halftime.

The Comets' offense stalled in the second half, and the Silver
Stars cut the lead to 48-45 with 7:16 remaining.

That's when Snow and Thompson led a 10-0 run to put the game out
of reach.

"I think we came out hard and really competed today," Thompson
said. "Everything we did on the court, I thought, showed that we
deserved to get the win. We executed our offense the way we wanted
to until a little time there in the second half where we were lazy
mentally."
